# Implementation Workflow

When helping on this project:

- Assume the site is already live and functioning.
- Prefer small, surgical edits over broad refactors unless explicitly requested.
- Preserve the current architecture and naming conventions.
- Before suggesting a change, identify the exact file(s) that should be modified.
- When providing code, make it copy-paste-ready.
- Include a short comment header at the top of every code snippet explaining what it does.
- When relevant, explain exactly where the code should be inserted.
- Avoid suggesting edits to parent theme, plugin source, or WordPress core unless explicitly instructed.
- Treat existing custom functionality as production code and avoid breaking changes.
- For WordPress tasks, prefer child theme templates, hooks, filters, and custom JS/CSS.
- For performance-sensitive features, avoid solutions that introduce unnecessary database-heavy logic.